- Potential to bury midrange detail: The Wall’s epic, anthemic passages and dense arrangements increase the risk that vocal detail and midrange piano presence will be obscured during dramatic moments—exactly the kind of production I said I avoid.
- Listening approach mismatch: The Wall rewards immersive, long‑form listening; I prefer albums that work as a compact, cozy single sitting of short, hooky tracks. The Wall’s strengths are real, but they are strengths for a different listener profile than the one I described.
